The paper focuses on training a policy for autonomous driving using imitation learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a perception system for preprocessing the input and a controller for executing the output on the car suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes using synthesized data to improve the robustness of the learned model, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the demonstration of the model driving a car in the real world suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
